      "name": "Infrastructure_Plan.html",
      "content": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n<title>Bloc 2: Infrastructure Plan</title>\n<style>\n  body { font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif; margin: 0; background: #0f172a; color: white; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; justify-content: center; height: 100vh; overflow: hidden; }\n  .presentation-wrapper { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; justify-content: center; width: 100%; height: 100%; }\n  .slide-container { width: 900px; height: 500px; background: white; color: #334155; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 20px 25px -5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); padding: 50px; position: relative; display: none; box-sizing: border-box; }\n  .slide-container.active { display: flex; flex-direction: column; animation: fadeIn 0.5s; }\n  @keyframes fadeIn { from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px); } to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); } }\n  .header { color: #0f172a; border-bottom: 3px solid #eab308; padding-bottom: 15px; margin-bottom: 25px; }\n  h1 { margin: 0; font-size: 2.2rem; }\n  h2 { color: #854d0e; font-size: 1.5rem; margin-top: 0; }\n  ul { font-size: 1.2rem; line-height: 1.8; color: #475569; }\n  .controls { margin-top: 30px; display: flex; gap: 15px; z-index: 10; }\n  button { padding: 12px 24px; cursor: pointer; background: #ca8a04; color: white; border: none; border-radius: 6px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1rem; }\n  button:hover { background: #a16207; }\n  button:disabled { background: #94a3b8; cursor: not-allowed; }\n  .slide-number { position: absolute; bottom: 20px; right: 30px; font-weight: bold; color: #94a3b8; }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<div class=\"presentation-wrapper\">\n  <div id=\"slides\">\n    <div class=\"slide-container active\">\n        <div class=\"header\"><h1>Aurora Tech: Data Architecture</h1></div>\n        <h2>Infrastructure Plan & Defense</h2>\n        <ul>\n            <li><strong>Objective:</strong> Design and document the PostgreSQL Data Warehouse infrastructure.</li>\n            <li><strong>Module:</strong> Bloc 2 - Architecture</li>\n            <li><strong>Duration:</strong> 5 minutes Defense</li>\n        </ul>\n        <div class=\"slide-number\">Slide 1 / 5</div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"slide-container\">\n        <div class=\"header\"><h1>1. Needs & Constraints</h1></div>\n        <h2>Why PostgreSQL + Docker?</h2>\n        <ul>\n            <li><strong>Reproducibility:</strong> Requires identical dev/prod environments (Infrastructure as Code).</li>\n            <li><strong>Relational Needs:</strong> SQL is required for the Star Schema design.</li>\n            <li><strong>Cost-efficiency:</strong> Open-source tools (PostgreSQL 15, Grafana) minimize licensing overhead.</li>\n        </ul>\n        <div class=\"slide-number\">Slide 2 / 5</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"slide-container\">\n        <div class=\"header\"><h1>2. Data Model</h1></div>\n        <h2>Star Schema Implementation</h2>\n        <div style=\"display:flex; justify-content:center; align-items:center; gap:20px; margin: 20px 0;\">\n            <div style=\"background:#fef08a; color:#854d0e; border: 2px solid #ca8a04; padding:15px; border-radius:8px; text-align:center; width: 140px;\"><b>dim_date</b><br/><small>PK: date_id</small></div>\n            <div style=\"font-size:1.5rem; color:#854d0e;\">&#10141;</div>\n            <div style=\"background:#4f46e5; color:white; padding:20px; border-radius:8px; text-align:center; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\"><b>fact_chromebook_margin_risk</b><br/><small>Metrics: eur_usd, freight_cost, delay</small></div>\n            <div style=\"font-size:1.5rem; color:#854d0e;\">&#11013;</div>\n            <div style=\"background:#fef08a; color:#854d0e; border: 2px solid #ca8a04; padding:15px; border-radius:8px; text-align:center; width: 140px;\"><b>dim_vendor</b><br/><small>PK: vendor_id</small></div>\n        </div>\n        <ul style=\"font-size: 1.1rem; margin-top: 10px;\">\n            <li>Optimized for fast aggregation queries required by the AI solution.</li>\n            <li>Decouples analytical processing from application overhead.</li>\n        </ul>\n        <div class=\"slide-number\">Slide 3 / 5</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"slide-container\">\n        <div class=\"header\"><h1>3. Infrastructure as Code</h1></div>\n        <h2>Containerization strategy</h2>\n        <ul>\n            <li><code>docker-compose.yml</code> provisions the database, pgAdmin console, and Grafana.</li>\n            <li>Volumes mapped securely: <code>./init.sql</code> applies schema on first boot automatically.</li>\n            <li>Virtual Network isolating database from public endpoints.</li>\n        </ul>\n        <div class=\"slide-number\">Slide 4 / 5</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"slide-container\">\n        <div class=\"header\"><h1>4. Observability & Demo</h1></div>\n        <h2>System Monitoring</h2>\n        <ul>\n            <li>Grafana deployed to monitor Postgres IOPS and CPU utilization during heavy ingestion.</li>\n            <li><em>Screencast submitted:</em> Demonstrates `docker-compose up`, verifying table creation and PgAdmin connectivity.</li>\n            <li><strong>Ready for Q&A.</strong></li>\n        </ul>\n        <div class=\"slide-number\">Slide 5 / 5</div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  \n  <div class=\"controls\">\n    <button id=\"prevBtn\" onclick=\"prevSlide()\" disabled>Previous Slide</button>\n    <button id=\"nextBtn\" onclick=\"nextSlide()\">Next Slide</button>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<script>\n  let currentSlide = 0;\n  const slides = document.querySelectorAll('.slide-container');\n  const prevBtn = document.getElementById('prevBtn');\n  const nextBtn = document.getElementById('nextBtn');\n\n  function showSlide(index) {\n    slides.forEach(s => s.classList.remove('active'));\n    slides[index].classList.add('active');\n    prevBtn.disabled = index === 0;\n    nextBtn.disabled = index === slides.length - 1;\n  }\n  function nextSlide() { if (currentSlide < slides.length - 1) { currentSlide++; showSlide(currentSlide); } }\n  function prevSlide() { if (currentSlide > 0) { currentSlide--; showSlide(currentSlide); } }\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>\n",
